\chapter{Git Repository Management}
\label{gitrepo}

We store the development log in a hidden Git repository
([[.learnlog/]]) inside the student's working directory.
We use Git's [[--git-dir]] and [[--work-tree]] flags so that
the student's files \emph{are} the working tree---no copying needed.
The [[.learnlog/]] directory contains only Git internals.

We use [[subprocess]] rather than GitPython to keep the package
dependency-free: Git is already installed on every lab machine, and our
operations are simple (init, add, commit, amend).

