\section{The [[LearnlogRepo]] class}

The class needs four operations: running Git commands, initialising the
repository, beginning a run (committing or amending), and finalising a
run (amending with results).
We introduce the class shell here and fill in each method in its own
section below.

<<classes>>=
class LearnlogRepo:
    """Manages a ``.learnlog/`` Git repository.

    Uses ``--git-dir=.learnlog --work-tree=.`` so the student's
    working directory is the work tree.  The ``.learnlog/`` directory
    contains only Git internals.
    """

    def __init__(self, workdir):
        self.workdir = pathlib.Path(workdir)
        self.git_dir = self.workdir / ".learnlog"
        self.env = {
            **os.environ,
            "GIT_DIR": str(self.git_dir),
            "GIT_WORK_TREE": str(self.workdir),
        }
        if not self.git_dir.exists():
            self.init_repo()

    <<repo methods>>
@

