\section{Running Git commands}

Every Git command needs the same environment variables and working
directory.
The [[git]] method wraps this boilerplate and returns the
[[CompletedProcess]] object for callers that need to inspect the result.
We set a 10-second timeout to prevent hangs from blocking the student's
program.

<<repo methods>>=
def git(self, *args):
    """Run a Git command with the learnlog environment.

    Returns the ``CompletedProcess`` object.  Raises no exception
    on non-zero exit codes---callers check ``returncode`` themselves.
    """
    return subprocess.run(
        ["git"] + list(args),
        cwd=str(self.workdir),
        env=self.env,
        capture_output=True,
        text=True,
        timeout=10,
    )
@

Let's verify the helper runs Git commands in the right context:

<<test functions>>=
def test_git_runs_command(workdir):
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    result = repo.git("status")
    assert result.returncode == 0
