\section{Repository initialisation}

On the very first run, we need to create the Git repository, configure
a committer identity, set up exclusion patterns, and make an initial
commit of all source files.

The learnlog repository inherits the student's global Git identity and
GPG signing configuration.
If a student has not configured Git at all, commits would fail---so we
set a fallback identity only when no global one exists.
This means commits are signed with the student's own key when available,
which is the right thing for a log of \emph{their} work.

<<repo methods>>=
def init_repo(self):
    """Initialise a new ``.learnlog/`` Git repository.

    Creates the repository, sets a fallback committer identity
    (only if the student has none configured globally), sets up
    exclusion patterns, and makes an initial commit of all files.
    """
    self.git("init")
    <<set fallback identity if needed>>

    <<set up exclude patterns>>
    <<initial commit>>
@

We check whether Git can resolve a user name; if not, we provide a
generic fallback.
This handles lab machines where students have never run
[[git config]].
We also disable GPG signing---these machine-generated commits do not
need cryptographic signatures, and students may not have a GPG key
configured:

<<set fallback identity if needed>>=
name_check = self.git("config", "user.name")
if name_check.returncode != 0:
    self.git("config", "user.name", "learnlog")
    self.git("config", "user.email", "learnlog@localhost")
self.git("config", "commit.gpgsign", "false")
@

The exclude file ([[.learnlog/info/exclude]]) keeps infrastructure
files out of the log.
We exclude [[.learnlog]] itself (to prevent recursion),
[[__pycache__]], virtual environments, and compiled bytecode.
If the student has a [[.learnlogignore]] file, we append its
patterns too---this is the only configuration hook, and it is empty by
default.

<<set up exclude patterns>>=
exclude_dir = self.git_dir / "info"
exclude_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
exclude_file = exclude_dir / "exclude"
patterns = [
    ".learnlog",
    "__pycache__",
    "*.pyc",
    ".venv",
    "venv",
    "env",
]
ignore_file = self.workdir / ".learnlogignore"
if ignore_file.exists():
    patterns.extend(
        ignore_file.read_text().splitlines()
    )
exclude_file.write_text(
    "\n".join(patterns) + "\n"
)
@

<<initial commit>>=
self.git("add", ".")
self.git(
    "commit",
    "--allow-empty",
    "-m",
    "learnlog: initial commit",
)
@

