\section{Formatting the run header}

The run header is a plain-text block with key--value fields.
We keep it simple---no YAML, no JSON---so it is easy to read in
[[git log]] output.

<<functions>>=
def format_run_header(script, args, start_time):
    """Format a run header block.

    The header records which script was run, its arguments, and
    the start time.
    """
    args_str = " ".join(args) if args else "(none)"
    return (
        f"Run: {script} {args_str}\n"
        f"\n"
        f"Script: {script}\n"
        f"Arguments: {args_str}\n"
        f"Start-Time: {start_time.isoformat()}"
    )
@

Let's verify the format:

<<test functions>>=
def test_format_run_header_basic():
    t = datetime.datetime(2026, 3, 20, 14, 30)
    header = format_run_header("hello.py", ["arg1"], t)
    assert "Run: hello.py arg1" in header
    assert "Script: hello.py" in header
    assert "Arguments: arg1" in header
    assert "Start-Time: 2026-03-20T14:30:00" in header

def test_format_run_header_no_args():
    t = datetime.datetime(2026, 3, 20, 14, 30)
    header = format_run_header("hello.py", [], t)
    assert "Arguments: (none)" in header
