\section{Finalising a run}

After the program finishes (or crashes), [[finalize_run]] amends the
current commit to append the I/O log, exception information, end time,
and exit code.
This completes the run block that [[begin_run]] started.

If the program was killed by SIGKILL, the [[atexit]] handler never
fires and [[finalize_run]] is never called.
The commit still exists with the run header from [[begin_run]], so we
know a run was attempted---the missing [[End-Time]] field signals
an abnormal termination.

<<repo methods>>=
def finalize_run(self, io_log, exception_info,
                 end_time, exit_code):
    """Complete the current run block with results.

    Amends the current commit to append I/O log, exception
    information, end time, and exit code.
    """
    existing = self.git(
        "log", "-1", "--format=%B"
    ).stdout.rstrip("\n")

    trailer = format_run_trailer(
        io_log, exception_info, end_time, exit_code
    )
    combined = existing + "\n" + trailer

    self.git("add", ".")
    self.git(
        "commit", "--amend", "--allow-empty",
        "-m", combined,
    )
@

Let's verify that finalisation completes the run block:

<<test functions>>=
def test_finalize_appends_io_and_exit(workdir):
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    now = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0)
    repo.begin_run("hello.py", [], now)
    end = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0, 5)
    repo.finalize_run(
        io_log="stdout: hello\n",
        exception_info=None,
        end_time=end,
        exit_code=0,
    )
    msg = repo.git("log", "-1", "--format=%B").stdout
    assert "End-Time:" in msg
    assert "Exit-Code: 0" in msg
    assert "stdout: hello" in msg
    assert "--- exception ---\nNone" in msg

def test_finalize_records_exception(workdir):
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    now = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0)
    repo.begin_run("hello.py", [], now)
    end = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0, 1)
    exc = "ValueError: bad input\n  File hello.py, line 1"
    repo.finalize_run(
        io_log="stderr: ValueError: bad input\n",
        exception_info=exc,
        end_time=end,
        exit_code=1,
    )
    msg = repo.git("log", "-1", "--format=%B").stdout
    assert "Exit-Code: 1" in msg
    assert "ValueError: bad input" in msg

def test_finalize_no_io(workdir):
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    now = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0)
    repo.begin_run("hello.py", [], now)
    end = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0, 1)
    repo.finalize_run(
        io_log="",
        exception_info=None,
        end_time=end,
        exit_code=0,
    )
    msg = repo.git("log", "-1", "--format=%B").stdout
    assert "(no I/O)" in msg
